# Dropdown / select menus

Use the shared `FormSelect` component (`src/components/ui/FormSelect.tsx`) for every dropdown or filter select. Do not add one-off `FilterSelect` implementations with custom CSS.

## Typography (from `FormSelect.module.css`)

- **Selected value** (trigger): `font-family: var(--font-display)`, `font-size: 16px`, `color: var(--text-primary)`. Sentence case in labels (e.g. "All sources", "CFO") — no `text-transform: uppercase` on the value.
- **Field label** (when shown): display font, uppercase label styling — only on the external `.label`, not on the selected value.
- **Menu options**: `font-size: 15px`, display font, normal casing.
- **Chevron**: `10px`, `var(--text-secondary)`.

## Usage

- Full field: pass `label="Role"` (or similar).
- Inline filter bar (label rendered separately): omit `label` or pass empty string; wrap with `className` for width only.
- Dropdown menu renders via portal to `document.body` (required inside glass / `backdrop-filter` panels).

## Example (filter bar)

```tsx
<FormSelect
  value={filter}
  onChange={(v) => setFilter(v)}
  options={[{ value: 'all', label: 'All sources' }, ...]}
  className={styles.filterSelect}
/>
```
